website_summaries.verdict: Some users may be disappointed with the copper/aluminum blend, but most drivers with emergency jump-start needs should be satisfied with the results when the need arises.
pros: Parrot clamps completely covered and insulated
2 gauge copper-plated aluminum wiring is commercial grade
Comparable models can cost three times its price point
cons: Some reports of flexibility problems in cold weather
Actual gauge may be higher than 2
Plastic parts can melt from overheated wiring during jump-starts

customer_reviews.title: More than adequate for my truck
customer_reviews.text: After doing the research and determining just how big of a cable i need to be able to jump start my truck - or jump start another truck from my truck, potentially in the wilderness, it became clear that this was exactly how big i needed. It's a great deal for what you get. Yes the wire is copper plated aluminum but it's not like I'm on the search and rescue team. My emergencies don't come about all that often, and even on frozen mornings i have found these cables supple enough.
customer_reviews.author: E. Jorgensen

customer_reviews.title: Finally, a REAL set of Cables
customer_reviews.text: Jumper cables are one of those things, you very seldome need them, but when you need them, you REALLY need them. I am sick of owning wimpy 4 or 8 gauge cables, and usually just barely long enough. These cables are very heavy duty, and at 25', you don't have to be as creative routing them from the 2 vehicles. This is really the only way to go, especially for the price. I fortunately have only used them once since I bought them a year ago, but it was a privilege and I feel I will own this one set of cables for the rest of my life. Very good investment.
customer_reviews.author: Espada

customer_reviews.title: Great cables!
customer_reviews.text: These are great cables. I am constantly getting compliments on them. My truck has a 28ft bed, so these work well for reaching equipment most anywhere on the bed. Quality is decent, and they transfer power fairly quickly, to be so long. I've been in the towing and recovery and specialized equipment hauling for over 25 years. I've dealt with a few sets of jumper cables in my time. The set I received are quality. I would order another set, if ever need be. I really don't see these, ever wearing out.
customer_reviews.author: TheJollySkipper

customer_reviews.title: great bang for the buck
customer_reviews.text: High quality, great bang for the buck. Easy to roll up and store. Great for longer motor-home like vehicles where reach might be important. Researched for days on the internet and FJC came up as one of the top sets of cables on a number of reviews. The pear shaped connectors have a full coating to prevent accidental contact and appear to be very strong. I have yet to use them, but my quick inspection upon arrival shows these to be a very good quality of cable, way beyond any previous pair I've owned in the last 40 years.
customer_reviews.author: OBG

customer_reviews.title: You never know...
customer_reviews.text: You never know if you will be able to park close enough to jump off a friend/family member in distress. With these long cables, you don't worry about that. With most cars and SUVs you can pull up to the BACK of the car in need and still jump it off with these cables. Are you a dad with kids who are driving? Have a friend who always leaves their lights on? Just like to be prepared? You can't go wrong with these cables. P.S. Look at the Bucket Boss 06100 Cable and Tool Bag to carry these in your ride!
customer_reviews.author: Winston Wolfe

customer_reviews.title: Great cables, Copper Coated Aluminum, Actual 2 ga
customer_reviews.text: Great cables. Bought 2 sets of these and 1 of another brand. These are copper coated aluminum 2 ga cables, with good rubber coating, and painted clamps. Compared to the other brand (Cal-Hawk) that was the same price on amazon, that were also supposed to be 2 ga 25ft, these are superior. The others were only 4 ga with thinner rubber coating that did not feel as pliable at lower temps. The others had rubber dipped handles on the clamps.
customer_reviews.author: Jeremy W

customer_reviews.title: Super Heavy Duty
customer_reviews.text: These are the best jumper cables I have ever owned and I have owned alot. They are 2 ga wire with extreamly heavy duty clips and I added a plug to one emd so I don't have to lift my hood to attach to my battery..... Absolutly fantastic cables worth three times the price...
customer_reviews.author: Richard A Drennan

customer_reviews.title: Get 25' you won't regret it
customer_reviews.text: These things are pretty nice...the clamps could be a little higher quality but they are still pretty nice (And honestly I feel that way about every pair of jumper cables). The cable is very flexible and what's cool about it is that it's 25'. Lets say your car is boxed in a parking lot so you can't pull another car beside it. No problem with these things, you can actually park a jumper car behind your car and run the cables all the way up to your dead battery.
customer_reviews.author: Jay

customer_reviews.title: Works great!
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this for my husband and he is very satisfied with it so far. He has already used these to jump off our 1 ton pickup, our tractor and our bulldozer. Heavy duty and the parrot clamps are nice. Good value for the price.
customer_reviews.author: L. Kemp

customer_reviews.title: Decent quality - not commercial but you are not paying for commercial either!
customer_reviews.text: Very good quality and reasonably rugged. Certainly plenty adequate for home and light farm use. I question the 2 gauge claim. Has to be the thinnest 2 gauge I have seen. Cables are very flexible which is definitely a plus (used them in 25 degree Fahrenheit weather) as some tend to be very awkward or you have to fight with them.
customer_reviews.author: Just added water

customer_reviews.title: Going to be hard to beat for this price.
customer_reviews.text: Great quality cables for the review. They aren't full copper core but for the price who would expect it to be. They appear to conduct and carry current just fine and they do stay flexible in very cold weather. I use these for rear mount winch and they do just fine. I actually cut one side of the clamps off and replaced it with an Anderson quick connect.
customer_reviews.author: wvrktguy

customer_reviews.title: Well Designed Booster Cables
customer_reviews.text: The FJC 45245 25' booster cable provides sufficient length to reach around a vehicle too close to an obstruction for direct battery access. In addition, the cables are quite flexible and the parrot clamps are sufficiently insulated so as to minimize the chances of having the clamp teeth touch each other.
customer_reviews.author: C. Fred Zeillemaker

customer_reviews.title: Great Product
customer_reviews.text: I own a roadside assistance business and these cables are a standard in my trunk as a backup to my Clore JNC660 jump box. The 25' length allows me to pull up to a car parked in a garage and still be able to reach. The 2 gauge cable thickness makes sure that I am able to get my customers going every time. The clamps themselves work okay on side terminal batteries and vehicles which are equipped with "jump posts".
customer_reviews.author: Chris H

customer_reviews.title: The real deal
customer_reviews.text: These are heavy and solid. The clamps work well. In a head-to-head trial they worked to jump-start a car with a completly dead battery on the first try; when using a lighter gauge set we couldn't even get the car to turn over. If you're going to carry jumper cables you might as well carry some that actually work.
customer_reviews.author: Steven

customer_reviews.title: A nice set of cables at a great price!
customer_reviews.text: These are well worth the price I paid for them. the diameter of the cable is spot on and the jacket is nice and thick. I purchased them to cut up and run the cable from the front of my jeep to my rear winch. Once I seen the parrot clamps I decided to make these my primary pair and cut up my old one.
customer_reviews.author: Joe

customer_reviews.title: Read the Reviews first and understand how these are made before spending your money.
customer_reviews.text: My fault. I saw the word "COPPER" and ordered these. After receiving them I cut the parrot jaws off one end of the set to install quick disconnects for my winch. Bad move on my part. The aluminum (copper coated) wire diameter was larger in diameter than 2 ga. I needed to trim it down before I could soldered in place. The insulating plastic was so "INEXPENSIVE" that by simply heating the copper connector, the heat transfer to the wire caused the plastic to swell. Again my fault. In the future, I will spend more time and carefully read the description(s) AND the on-line reviews. Regards. I recommend solid copper wire for cold weather applications. Bob
customer_reviews.author: Robert Evoy

customer_reviews.text: these cables carry the juice when needed,with the cables being so long you can pull up behind the car you wanna jump start instead of alongside in those tight situations. a little difficult to clamp onto side post batteries but I really haven't had a set that was good for that,side post batteries are a bad design to begin with for jump starting.
